verbose_text: Furthermore, given the observed correlation between neuronal and ventral forebrain gene expression and the known role of the Wnt / beta-catenin pathway in promoting progenitor proliferation during early cortical development, differences in Wnt / beta-catenin signaling levels may concurrently be linked to differences in patterning and differences in the proportion of progenitors and neurons in culture.
evidence: Wnt/beta-catenin pathway in promoting progenitor proliferation
